"signal_description": "Calculate the percentage of purchase order items that were released more than 3 days after creation from the defaultview-124 table.

1. Select the total number of cases (purchase order items) from the defaultview-124 table and store it as 'Total No. of Cases'.
2. Select the number of cases where the time between the last 'Release PO' event and the first 'Create PO Item' event is greater than 3 days. Store this as 'Released 3 Days Later'. 
3. Divide 'Released 3 Days Later' by 'Total No. of Cases' and multiply by 100 to get the percentage."  
}
